<dl id="n54146c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54146c">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54146c"> 146(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> stone, cult of <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54146c"><li>FW 279.02 </li><li><a href="../../flex/lf/lexlf.htm#n54146c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/lf/l39lf.htm#n54146c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54146c">MS BL 47478-339</ms> </li><li>JJA 53:318 <a name="lad13" href="../../FF/fdra/lda.htm#lfd4">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/lf/lfd4.htm#n54146c">Draft: II.2&sect;7.4</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&laquo;Les pierres, dit M. Leenhardt en une formule frappante, sont l&apos;esprit p&eacute;trifi&eacute; des anc&ecirc;tres.&raquo; En Nouvelle-Cal&eacute;donie comme en beaucoup d&apos;autres r&eacute;gions, <mark>les pierres poss&egrave;dent par elles-m&ecirc;mes une valeur mystique</mark> qui les pr&eacute;destine, pour ainsi dire, &agrave; la fonction de symboles. La duret&eacute; qui leur permet de se conserver ind&eacute;finiment en fait des &ecirc;tres privil&eacute;gi&eacute;s. Aux yeux des, primitifs, loin de n&apos;&ecirc;tre que des morceaux de mati&egrave;re inorganique, inanim&eacute;e, insensible, elles sont les &ecirc;tres, de la nature les plus richement dou&eacute;s de force, de mana, puisqu&apos;elles ne s&apos;affaiblissent jamais et que sur elles la maladie ni la mort n&apos;ont de prise. <br>["Stones," says Leenhardt in a striking formula, "are the petrified spirit of ancestors. In New Caledonia, as in many other regions, the stones themselves have a mystical value which predestines them, so to speak, for the function of symbols. The hardness that allows them to keep indefinitely makes them privileged beings. In the eyes of the primitive people, far from being nothing but pieces of inorganic, inanimate, insensitive matter, they are the beings, of nature, most richly endowed with strength and mana, since they never weaken and only disease and death have no hold over them. <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 204</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
